[DhtmlXQ_comment17]Checkmate.||||Conclusion: ||When your elephant or advisor is under attack, the following must be noted:||1) if you choose to defend and protect the advisor and elephant under attack, you must make sure that  the opponent does not have any further attack after protecting it. ||2) if you decide to sacrifice your advisor/elephant, you must make sure that you attack in the correct direction, and the speed of your attack must be faster that your opponent's||3) if you do not have a chance to launch a counter, protecting your advisor/elephant would be  necessary||4) when your opponent has a cannon, protecting your elephant would be important. if your opponent is attacking with his horse or pawns, advisors would play a more important defensive role.||5) when you try to attack your opponent's advisors and elephants (2nd example), you must make sure that he is unable to counterattack[/DhtmlXQ_comment17]
